# Injection Context

An injection context is a place where you have access to the `inject` function.

## Valid injection context

### Class

Within a component, service, or directive class (a class decorated with `@Component`, `@Injectable`, or `@Directive`)

This includes code inside the `constructor` block or class property initializers.

```typescript showLineNumbers
class Foo {
  private service1 = inject(service1);

  constructor() {
    const something = inject(something);
  }
}
```

### Factory function

A function passed to `useFactory` of a [`Provider`](https://angular.dev/api/core/Provider) or <Color color="var(--can-not-understand-font-color)">an [`@Injectable`](https://angular.dev/api/core/Injectable)</Color>

It also includes a factory function for [`InjectionToken`](https://angular.dev/api/core/InjectionToken).

### API that run in an injection context

Some APIs run inside an injection context, so it is valid to use `inject`.

For example, router guards such as `CanActivateFn`.

```typescript showLineNumbers
const canActivateTeam: CanActivateFn = (route, state) => {
  // highlight-next-line
  return inject(someservice);
};
```

## Manually run code block in injection context

Wrap the code block with [`runInInjectionContext`](https://angular.dev/api/core/runInInjectionContext).

```typescript showLineNumbers
@Injectable()
export class HeroService {
  // highlight-next-line
  private environmentInjector = inject(EnvironmentInjector);

  someMethod() {
    // highlight-start
    runInInjectionContext(this.environmentInjector, () => {
      inject(SomeService);
    });
    // highlight-end
  }
}
```

<Aside type="note" title="note">

[`runInInjectionContext`](https://angular.dev/api/core/runInInjectionContext) requires an [`EnvironmentInjector`](https://angular.dev/api/core/EnvironmentInjector).

</Aside>

